    "title": {
        "rendered": "What is an excerpt? (Classic Editor)"
    },
    "content": {
        "rendered": "\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What is an excerpt</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Excerpt is an optional text associated to a Post. Most of the time, it is used as the <strong>Post summary</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"710\" height=\"235\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/WordPress-Excerpt-editor.jpg\" alt=\"WordPress Excerpt metabox\" class=\"wp-image-10851380\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/WordPress-Excerpt-editor.jpg 710w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/WordPress-Excerpt-editor-300x99.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 710px) 100vw, 710px\" /><figcaption>WordPress excerpt metabox</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Not finding the Excerpt editing box? Check your Post&#8217;s <strong>Screen Options</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Regarding the Theme you are using on your site, Excerpts can be displayed on different pages (search results, archives, etc.).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If Excerpt is empty, WordPress automatically creates an excerpt using the first 55 words of the post.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to display excerpts on the posts page</h2>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>Go to <strong>Settings &gt; Reading</strong>.</li><li>Scroll to <strong>For each article in a feed, show</strong>.</li><li>Select <strong>Summary</strong>.</li></ol>\n",
        "protected": false
    },
    "excerpt": {
        "rendered": "<p>What is an excerpt Excerpt is an optional text associated to a Post. Most of the time, it is used as the Post summary. Not finding the Excerpt editing box? Check your Post&#8217;s Screen Options. Regarding the Theme you are using on your site, Excerpts can be displayed on different pages (search results, archives, etc.). [&hellip;]</p>\n",
